text: Buffalo County is a county located in the U.S. state of South Dakota. As of the 2020 census, 1,948 people lived there. Its county seat is Gann Valley which, at 10 people, is the least populous county seat in the United States. It was created in 1864. as part of the Dakota Territory. == References == Category:South Dakota counties Category:1870s establishments in Dakota Territory Category:1871 establishments in the United States
